7.1 Navigation Basics – React Navigation Introduction:-
:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::

Almost every mobile application has multiple screens. Users move between these screens using navigation.

Examples:

Instagram → Home → Profile → Settings

WhatsApp → Chats → Status → Calls

YouTube → Home → Video → Channel

To manage screen transitions in React Native, developers commonly use a library called React Navigation.

What is React Navigation?:-
..................................

React Navigation is the most popular navigation library for React Native apps.

It allows developers to:

Navigate between screens

Manage navigation stacks

Pass data between screens

Create tab bars and drawer menus

Think of it like:

| Technology   | Equivalent           |
| ------------ | -------------------- |
| Android      | Navigation Component |
| Flutter      | Navigator            |
| React Native | React Navigation     |


Types of Navigation:- 

React Navigation supports several navigation patterns:
| Navigation Type     | Use Case              |
| ------------------- | --------------------- |
| Stack Navigation    | screen-to-screen flow |
| Tab Navigation      | bottom tabs           |
| Drawer Navigation   | side menu             |
| Material Navigation | Android-style tabs    |

Navigation Methods:- 
::::::::::::::::::::::::

Common navigation methods:
| Method     | Description           |
| ---------- | --------------------- |
| navigate() | move to screen        |
| goBack()   | go to previous screen |
| push()     | push new screen       |
| replace()  | replace screen        |


