7.3 Navigation Patterns:- 
::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::

Navigation patterns define how screens communicate and interact within the navigation system.

Example real apps:

Instagram → open profile with user ID

YouTube → open video via URL

WhatsApp → nested chat navigation

:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
1️⃣ Passing Parameters:- 
:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::

Often when navigating, we need to send data from one screen to another.

Example:

Product List Screen
      ↓
Product Details Screen

The details screen needs the product ID.

Passing Parameters

Example:

navigation.navigate("Profile", {name:"Ritesh", age:25})

Here we pass an object of parameters.

Accessing Parameters

Inside the destination screen:

function ProfileScreen({route}){

const {name, age} = route.params

return(
<Text>{name} - {age}</Text>
)

}
Full Example
import React from 'react'
import {View, Text, Button} from 'react-native'

function HomeScreen({navigation}){

return(

<View>

<Button
title="Open Profile"
onPress={()=> navigation.navigate("Profile", {name:"Ritesh"})}
/>

</View>

)

}

function ProfileScreen({route}){

const {name} = route.params

return(
<Text>Hello {name}</Text>
)

}
Updating Screen Params

Sometimes you need to update parameters.

Example:

navigation.setParams({name:"Amit"})

This updates the route parameters.

